## Rules

- 1–8 verified members; founders/leadership prioritized.
- `memberName`: full real name. Reject pseudonyms unless they're the public identity (e.g., `0xMaki`).
- `memberPosition`: brief title (`CEO`, `Co-Founder`, `Head of Engineering`).
- `oneLiner`: ≤140 chars on prior notable experience. Use `null` when nothing verifiable is found. Never write placeholder text such as `Unverified`, `TBD`, `N/A`, `暂未提供`, or any "fill this later" sentence.
- `avatarUrl`: always `null`. Do not construct unavatar / X / GitHub URLs. Deterministic normalizers fill this field post-R2 from RootData project candidates first, then direct RootData person search, then paid Unavatar from verified `memberLink` social profiles when RootData has no usable avatar. The image is downloaded under `out/protocol-member-logo/` and rewritten to the OneKey static-logo CDN path.
- `memberLink.xLink`: full URL `https://x.com/<handle>` or null.
- `memberLink.linkedinLink`: full LinkedIn profile URL or null.
- Cross-check: a candidate appearing in rootdata + X bio confirming the role + LinkedIn matching = include. Less than 2 of these = exclude. If the member is included but prior experience cannot be verified, set `oneLiner` to `null` and emit a gap.

